724371f-a.text:
West Broadway, east side, at Chambers Street, and showing the Cosmopolitan Hotel (the N.E. corner), across the Sixth Ave. Elevated Line. Prominent
building shown, is the Woolworth Tower.
December 25, 1936.
P. L. Sperr.
This hotel is about 80 years old, and was the rendezvous of politicians, judges and lawyers. Its owner for many years was the late Joseph M. Weintraub. See the New York Times, November 12, 1937 for an account of a fire that swept
the upper floors on the 11th.
